text.headline: Development Timeline of Mimi Lam
text.text: Welcome to my timeline! Here you will see my growth and journey to becoming a computer programmer throughout the years, all the way from the beginning.

text.headline: Website Design
text.text: In my sophomore year of high school, I took a website design course that taught how to use Adobe Dreamweaver to create websites.

text.headline: AP Computer Science A
text.text: In my junior year of high school, I decided to challenge myself by taking Advanced Placement (AP) Computer Science A, an introductory college-level course teaching the Java programming language. Things started to take off from here!

text.headline: AP Computer Science Principles
text.text: Continuing the trend of taking at least one computer science course each year, I challenged myself again by taking Advanced Placement (AP) Computer Science Principles, an introductory college-level course that focused on the big ideas of computer science.
